<div class="section">
    <h2>Fan Logistics & Pro-Tips</h2>
    
    <h3>Arrival & Parking</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Free Parking:</strong> Lot 3 (across from the track behind Bass Pro Shops) is typically free but requires a long walk across the pedestrian bridge.</li>
        <li><strong>Paid Parking:</strong> Lot 4 (near Turn 4) is closer but fills up fast and requires a pre-purchased permit.</li>
        <li><strong>The Tram System:</strong> Use the free trams to move between the Infield and the Grandstands. They run 24 hours but expect long lines right after the start and before the finish.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>What to Bring (and Bag Policy)</h3>
    <p class="highlight">Max Bag Size: 18x18x14 inches. Soft-sided coolers: 14x14x14 inches.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Layering is Key:</strong> Florida in January can be 70°F during the day and drop to 30°F at night. Bring a heavy jacket and a blanket for the 3:00 AM stint.</li>
        <li><strong>Noise Protection:</strong> Earplugs or noise-canceling headsets are mandatory for comfort—the GTP prototypes and GTD cars are deafening in the canyons of the grandstands.</li>
        <li><strong>Food & Drink:</strong> You can bring your own food and alcohol (no glass containers). This is the best way to save money over 24 hours.</li>
        <li><strong>Comfort:</strong> Metal-frame chairs are prohibited in the stands, but soft seat cushions are highly recommended for the aluminum bleachers.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="tips">
        <strong>Insider Tip:</strong> Visit the <strong>Hard Rock Bet Fanzone</strong> to sign the start/finish line on Saturday morning and get up close to the cars in the garages during the night!
    </div>
</div>

<div class="section">
    <h2>Where to Watch</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>The Grandstands:</strong> Best for seeing the entire track and the pits. At night, the sight of brake rotors glowing cherry-red entering Turn 1 is iconic.</li>
        <li><strong>The Infield (Turn 1 / International Horseshoe):</strong> High-action overtaking zones. Great for photography.</li>
        <li><strong>The Ferris Wheel:</strong> Located in the Midway, it offers the most famous view of the track at night (additional cost).</li>
    </ul>
</div>

<div class="footer">
    <p>Enjoy the 64th running of North America's greatest endurance race!</p>
    <p><em>Check the official Daytona International Speedway app for real-time schedule updates and gate information.</em></p>
</div>

